# File Transfer Between Two Ubuntu Virtual Machines Using SCP

## Aim

To transfer files from one Ubuntu Virtual Machine to another Ubuntu Virtual Machine using SCP (Secure Copy Protocol).

---

# Step 1 — Install VirtualBox

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install virtualbox -y
```

Launch VirtualBox:

```bash
virtualbox
```

---

# Step 2 — Download Ubuntu ISO

Download Ubuntu Disk:

https://portal.cloud.hashicorp.com/vagrant/discover/bento/ubuntu-16.04


---

# Step 3 — Create First VM

Open VirtualBox:

```text
New → Name: Ubuntu1
Type: Linux
Version: Ubuntu (64-bit)
```

Use an Existing Virtual Hard Disk File

select: 
ubuntu-18.04-amd64-disk001

Create:

```text
Username: om
Password: om123
```

---

# Step 4 — Create Second VM

Repeat same steps.

```text
Name: Ubuntu2
Username: om
Password: om123
```

---

# Step 5 — Configure Network

For BOTH VMs:

```text
Settings → Network → Adapter 1 → Bridged Adapter
```

Click OK.

---

# Step 6 — Start Both VMs

Open terminal in BOTH Ubuntu VMs.

---

# Step 7 — Install SSH

Run on BOTH VMs:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openssh-server -y
```

Start SSH:

```bash
sudo systemctl start ssh
```

Enable SSH:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable ssh
```

Check SSH status:

```bash
sudo systemctl status ssh
```

Expected output:

```text
active (running)
```

---

# Step 8 — Find IP Address

Run on BOTH VMs:

```bash
hostname -I
```

Example:

VM1:

```text
192.168.1.10
```

VM2:

```text
192.168.1.20
```

---

# Step 9 — Create File in VM1

Run on VM1:

```bash
echo "Hello from VM1" > file.txt
```

Check file:

```bash
cat file.txt
```

---

# Step 10 — Transfer File From VM1 to VM2

Run on VM1:

```bash
scp file.txt om@192.168.1.20:/home/om/
```

Enter password:

```text
om123
```

---

# Step 11 — Verify File in VM2

Run on VM2:

```bash
ls
```

Read file:

```bash
cat file.txt
```

Expected output:

```text
Hello from VM1
```

